{
  "texts": [
    "The Open Slide program was used to access all the image slides 54.",
    "WSIs often have at least a 50% white background, as the white background in WSI analysis carries no useful information and can obstruct classification.",
    "Background filtering is a crucial preprocessing step.",
    "Different techniques have been tried to get rid of the background, such as color thresholding and morphological operations.",
    "This model uses a straightforward color thresholding technique that examines each pixel's green channel values and eliminates any that are more than the 200-intensity threshold."
  ]
}